(43, 5, 26, 43, 11, 26, 26, 'life in himself', 'Connection of Life in Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of life granted by God. John 5:26 states that the Son has life in himself, while John 11:26 assures that believers in Christ shall never die, linking the divine source of life to eternal life through faith.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 26, 2, 3, 14, 14, 'life in himself', 'Connection of Divine Life', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of inherent life. John 5:26 speaks of the Son having life in himself, while Exodus 3:14 reveals God as the self-existent ''I AM.'' This connection highlights the nature of divine existence and life.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 26, 46, 15, 45, 45, 'life in himself', 'Connection of Life and Spirit', 'This connection highlights the theme of life as it relates to both the Father and the Son. The phrase ''life in himself'' in John 5:26 parallels the concept of the ''quickening spirit'' in 1 Corinthians 15:45, emphasizing the transformative power of life given through Christ.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 26, 54, 1, 17, 17, 'life in himself', 'Connection of Divine Life', 'This connection highlights the theme of life inherent in God and the Son. Both passages emphasize the eternal nature of God, with John 5:26 stating that the Father has life in Himself, while 1 Timothy 1:17 describes God as eternal and immortal.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 26, 24, 10, 10, 10, 'life in himself', 'Connection of Divine Life', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of life in God. John 5:26 speaks of the Son having life in himself, while Jeremiah 10:10 refers to the Lord as the living God, highlighting the divine nature of life.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 26, 19, 36, 9, 9, 'life in himself', 'Life and Light Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of life as a divine attribute. Both passages emphasize the source of life, with John noting the Son''s possession of life and Psalms referencing God as the fountain of life.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 27, 44, 10, 42, 42, 'authority to execute judgment', 'Judgment Authority Connection', 'This connection highlights the authority of Jesus as the Judge, as indicated in both passages. John 5:27 emphasizes His role as the one given authority to execute judgment, while Acts 10:42 refers to Him as the Judge of the living and the dead.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 27, 43, 5, 22, 22, 'authority to execute judgment', 'Judgment Authority of the Son', 'Both passages emphasize the authority of the Son in executing judgment. John 5:22 states that all judgment is committed to the Son, while John 5:27 affirms that he has been given authority to execute judgment as the Son of man.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 27, 44, 17, 31, 31, 'because he is the Son of man', 'Judgment by the Son of Man', 'Both passages emphasize the authority of Jesus to execute judgment. John 5:27 highlights his role as the Son of man, while Acts 17:31 refers to the man ordained to judge the world, linking them through the theme of divine judgment.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 27, 27, 7, 13, 14, 'Son of man', 'Judgment and Authority Connection', 'This connection highlights the authority given to the ''Son of man'' in both passages. John 5:27 states that he has authority to execute judgment, while Daniel 7:14 describes the ''Son of man'' receiving dominion and a kingdom.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 27, 46, 15, 25, 25, 'because he is the Son of man', 'Authority and Reign of Christ', 'This connection highlights the authority given to Jesus as the Son of man in executing judgment, which aligns with His reign over all enemies. Both passages emphasize the theme of Christ''s sovereign authority in judgment and rule.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 27, 60, 3, 22, 22, 'authority to execute judgment', 'Authority and Judgment Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the authority given to Christ. John 5:27 highlights His role in executing judgment, while 1 Peter 3:22 notes that all powers are made subject to Him.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 27, 19, 110, 6, 6, 'authority to execute judgment', 'Judgment Authority Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of judgment, as both passages emphasize the authority to judge. John 5:27 mentions the authority given to the Son of man, while Psalms 110:6 describes judgment among the heathen.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 28, 66, 20, 12, 12, 'all that are in the graves', 'Resurrection and Judgment Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of resurrection and judgment. Both passages refer to the dead being called forth and judged, emphasizing the significance of their works.', 'theme', 0.44699999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 28, 52, 4, 14, 17, 'shall hear his voice', 'Resurrection of the Dead', 'This connection highlights the theme of resurrection, as both passages speak about the dead hearing a voice and rising. John 5:28 mentions those in graves hearing His voice, while 1 Thessalonians 4:14-17 describes the dead in Christ rising at the Lord''s coming.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 28, 23, 26, 19, 19, 'all that are in the graves', 'Resurrection of the Dead', 'Both passages emphasize the resurrection of the dead. John 5:28 speaks of those in graves hearing His voice, while Isaiah 26:19 declares that the dead shall arise. This connection highlights a shared theme of life after death.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 28, 46, 15, 42, 54, 'all that are in the graves shall hear his voice', 'Resurrection of the Dead', 'Both passages emphasize the resurrection of the dead, with John 5:28 stating that all in the graves will hear His voice, while 1 Corinthians 15:42-54 elaborates on the transformation from corruption to incorruption. This connection highlights the promise of life after death and the change that occurs at resurrection.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 28, 43, 11, 24, 25, 'all that are in the graves', 'Resurrection and Life Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the resurrection of the dead. John 5:28 speaks of all in graves hearing His voice, while John 11:24-25 highlights belief in resurrection through Jesus.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 28, 18, 19, 25, 26, 'all that are in the graves', 'Resurrection and Redemption Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the resurrection of the dead. John speaks of all in graves hearing His voice, while Job expresses hope in seeing God after death, indicating a future restoration.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 28, 43, 6, 39, 40, NULL, 'Resurrection at the Last Day', 'This connection highlights the theme of resurrection in both passages. John 5:28 speaks of all in the graves hearing His voice, while John 6:39-40 emphasizes raising believers at the last day.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 29, 27, 12, 2, 3, 'resurrection of life', 'Resurrection and Judgment Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the resurrection of individuals based on their deeds, with outcomes of life or contempt. The phrases ''resurrection of life'' and ''everlasting life'' highlight this theme of judgment.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 29, 45, 2, 6, 10, 'resurrection of life', 'Resurrection and Judgment Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the outcomes of one''s deeds, linking good actions to eternal life and evil actions to condemnation. This connection highlights the principle of divine judgment based on moral behavior.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 29, 44, 24, 15, 15, NULL, 'Resurrection of the Dead', 'Both passages emphasize the resurrection of the dead, distinguishing between the just and unjust. John 5:29 speaks of the resurrection of life for the good, while Acts 24:15 mentions a resurrection for both the just and unjust.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 29, 40, 25, 31, 46, 'resurrection of life; and they that have done evil', 'Resurrection and Judgment Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the separation of the righteous and the wicked at the time of judgment, leading to either eternal life or punishment. John 5:29 speaks of a resurrection based on one''s deeds, while Matthew 25:31-46 illustrates this judgment through the metaphor of sheep and goats.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 29, 42, 14, 14, 14, 'resurrection of life', 'Resurrection of the Just', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of resurrection, specifically the outcomes based on one''s actions. John 5:29 speaks of a resurrection leading to life or damnation, while Luke 14:14 refers to being recompensed at the resurrection of the just.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 29, 48, 6, 8, 10, 'resurrection of life', 'Resurrection and Reaping Themes', 'Both passages emphasize the outcomes of one''s actions, highlighting the contrast between good and evil. John 5:29 speaks of the resurrection of life for the good, while Galatians 6:8-10 discusses reaping life everlasting for those who sow to the Spirit.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 29, 54, 6, 18, 18, 'done good', 'Connection of Good Works', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of doing good. John 5:29 speaks of the resurrection of those who have done good, while 1 Timothy 6:18 encourages being rich in good works.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 30, 43, 6, 38, 38, NULL, 'Connection of Divine Will', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of seeking the will of the Father. They highlight Jesus'' submission to divine authority rather than personal desire.', 'theme', 0.552, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
